definition.value: The conjugate base of thiomorpholine-3-carboxylic acid.

A branched amino octasaccharide derivative that is beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the mannosyl group is substituted at position 3 by a beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man group and at position 6 by an alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man group, while the D-GlcNAc residue at the reducing end is substituted at position 6 by an alpha-L-Fuc residue.

A branched amino octasaccharide derivative that is beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc in which the mannosyl group is substituted at position 3 by a beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man group and at position 6 by an alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-alpha-D-Man group, while the D-GlcNAc residue at the reducing end is substituted at position 6 by an alpha-L-Fuc residue.

An amino hexasaccharide derivative that is beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the mannosyl group is substituted at position 6 by an alpha-D-Man residue and at position 3 by a beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man group.
A glycosyl alditol consisting of beta-D-glucopyranose and D-glucitol residues joined in sequence by a (1->4) glycosidic bond.
